  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "G2BmtrKcGeoQuodVqix9i1N6QZc=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:38.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# nullable input types require explicit coalescing to match state types\n\nOptional input types and optional state types have different nullability:\n\n- **Input**: `InputMaybe<T>` = `null | undefined | T`\n- **State**: `Maybe<T>` = `T | null`\n\nTypeScript won't accept `undefined` where `null` is expected, so you must coalesce:\n\n```typescript\n// \u274c Type error \u2014 undefined not assignable to T | null\namount: action.input.amount,\nnotes: action.input.notes,\n\n// \u2705 Correct \u2014 coalesce to match Maybe<T>\namount: action.input.amount || null,\nnotes: action.input.notes || [],\n```\n\nSince [[truthy checks are safer than undefined checks for optional state assignment]], prefer `if (action.input.field)` over `if (action.input.field !== undefined)` for conditional updates.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[reducer patterns]]\n- [[gotchas]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:38.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:38.000Z"
    }
  },
